{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1772637254,"nonce":"OFNsPThWnnjsFqw5B9APE0bS4/c=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87uT3Uh","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/343#issuecomment-3998184737"},"message":"## Design Note: Helper Script to Reduce Permission Prompts\n\nDuring the manual test of this concept on PR #341, we identified that each `gh api` and `git` command triggers a separate permission prompt in Claude Code. A helper script would consolidate these into a single prompt.\n\n### Proposed: `.agent/scripts/fetch_copilot_reviews.sh \u003cPR-number\u003e`\n\nThe script would:\n\n1. Get the HEAD commit timestamp\n2. Fetch all Copilot review IDs and timestamps via `gh api`\n3. Filter to reviews submitted after HEAD\n4. Fetch comments for those reviews\n5. Output structured JSON to stdout\n\n### Benefits\n\n- **One permission prompt** instead of 3-4 separate ones (git log, gh api for reviews, gh api for comments)\n- The skill then evaluates comments using local file reads (Read tool), which require no prompts\n- Total permission prompts reduced from ~5+ to ~1 per invocation\n\n### Output Format (draft)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pr\": 341,\n  \"head_timestamp\": \"2026-03-04T09:07:59-05:00\",\n  \"reviews_after_head\": [\n    {\n      \"review_id\": 3889726232,\n      \"submitted_at\": \"2026-03-04T14:19:50Z\",\n      \"comments\": [\n        {\n          \"path\": \"path/to/file\",\n          \"line\": 42,\n          \"body\": \"comment text...\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772639228,"nonce":"/e/bTrMcNtEvhgCV//ipqScFePg=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87uUrKe","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/343#issuecomment-3998397086"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — the skill is read-only (triage + plan, no auto-fix), produces in-conversation output, and follows established skill patterns. A single PR can deliver the skill file plus the helper script.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — this is workspace infrastructure (agent skill + helper script), not project-specific content.\n\n**Dependencies**: The design note comment proposes a helper script (`.agent/scripts/fetch_copilot_reviews.sh`). This should be included in the same PR rather than split out, since the skill depends on it for usability.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Human control and transparency | OK | Plan-only output; user decides what to fix. Good design choice. |\n| Enforcement over documentation | OK | No new rules introduced; skill is a workflow aid. |\n| Capture decisions, not just implementations | Watch | The \"since last commit\" filter and \"plan only, no auto-fix\" are design decisions worth capturing. The issue body documents rationale well — consider whether an ADR is warranted if this becomes a pattern for other external-review triage skills. |\n| A change includes its consequences | Watch | The skill list in framework adapters (`copilot-instructions.md`, `gemini-cli.instructions.md`, `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`) must be updated. The consequences map flags this. Also update the script reference table in `AGENTS.md` if the helper script is added. |\n| Only what's needed | OK | Solves a concrete, recurring pain point (manually triaging Copilot comments). The helper script consolidation is a pragmatic response to permission-prompt friction. |\n| Improve incrementally | OK | Standalone skill; doesn't require changes to existing skills or workflows. |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | OK | Generic workspace tooling — works with any PR in any repo. |\n| Primary framework first, portability where free | OK | Claude Code skill, appropriately framework-specific. The helper script is portable (plain bash + `gh`). |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0001 — Adopt ADRs | No | Workflow skill, not an architectural decision. The issue body captures design rationale sufficiently. |\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | Yes (passes) | Skill is generic — not coupled to any project repo. |\n| 0004 — Enforcement hierarchy | No | No new compliance rules introduced. |\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | Watch | If the helper script is added to `.agent/scripts/`, the script reference table in `AGENTS.md` should be updated. |\n\n### Consequences\n\nFrom the consequences map, adding a framework skill triggers:\n- Update skill lists in non-Claude adapters (`.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md`, `.agent/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`)\n- Update the framework adapter file (`CLAUDE.md`) if needed\n\nIf the helper script is added to `.agent/scripts/`:\n- Update the script reference table in `AGENTS.md`\n- Update `Makefile` if it should have a target (likely not needed for this script)\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Include the helper script (`fetch_copilot_reviews.sh`) in the same PR as the skill — the design note makes a strong case for it.\n- Ensure the \"since last commit\" filter handles edge cases: what if there are no commits yet on the branch, or if the PR has force-pushed? A brief note in the skill doc about expected behavior would help.\n- The skill description says \"comments newer than HEAD\" — clarify whether this is HEAD's author date or committer date, as rebases can make these diverge.\n- Consider how the skill handles a PR with zero Copilot comments (early exit with a clear message).\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772644683,"nonce":"F7VT1A5RKQbj5pE/GP3rLE0MB5U=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87vvuuZzwAAAAVq3zNl"},"status":2}]}